# No file existed here at all before, so `COPY . .` in apps/api/Dockerfile
# and apps/web/Dockerfile copied the host's own node_modules (Windows
# symlinks, wrong platform binaries) over the container's freshly
# `pnpm install`-ed Linux node_modules, breaking module resolution
# (e.g. "Cannot find module '.../node_modules/typescript/bin/tsc'").
# Never caught in Dokploy, which clones fresh from git server-side with no
# local node_modules to leak in — only surfaced when testing `docker build`
# from an already-`pnpm install`-ed local working directory.

**/node_modules
# Keep .git in the build context: the web build derives /version.json and the visible build badge from git metadata during docker build, and Dokploy builds directly from a cloned repo rather than from a pre-generated artifact.
.turbo
.cache
**/.cache
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage
.worktrees
.claude
.vscode
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.log
